		<section xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.identities">
		<title>Notable Identities</title>	  
			  <para>
			  <informaltable class="identitylist">
				<tbody>
				  <tr>
				    <td><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>H</replaceable></td>
				    <td> = </td>
				    <td><code><![CDATA[(]]></code><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable><code><![CDATA[)]]></code><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>H</replaceable></td>
				    <td>  (Left Associative)</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>H</replaceable></td>
				    <td> = </td>
				    <td><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]><![CDATA[(]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>H</replaceable><code><![CDATA[)]]></code></td>
				    <td>  (Right Associative)</td>
				  </tr>
				  <tr>
				    <td><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable></td>
				    <td> = </td>
				    <td><replaceable>G</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>F</replaceable></td>
				    <td>  (Commutative)</td>
				  </tr>
				</tbody>
				</informaltable>
			  </para>
    	</section>
    
	  <section xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.behavior">
		  <title>Behavior</title>		  
		  <para>
		  <variablelist>
			<varlistentry><term><replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable></term>
			<listitem>
			<para>
			  Execution of expression <replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable>
			   occurs by executing <replaceable>F</replaceable> 
			  and <replaceable>G</replaceable> concurrently. Whenever <replaceable>F</replaceable> or <replaceable>G</replaceable> communicates with a service or 
			  <ind>publishes</ind> a value, <replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable> does so as well.
			  Therefore, <replaceable>F</replaceable><code><![CDATA[ | ]]></code><replaceable>G</replaceable> interleaves 
			  the publications of <replaceable>F</replaceable>
			  and <replaceable>G</replaceable> arbitrarily.
		    </para>
			</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			</variablelist>
		  </para>
	  </section>
	  
	  <section xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.type">
	    <title>Type</title>
			<para>
				The type of <replaceable>F</replaceable> <code>|</code> <replaceable>G</replaceable> is the <link linkend="ref.types.lattice">join</link> of the types of <replaceable>F</replaceable> and <replaceable>G</replaceable>.
			</para>
		</section>
	  
	  <section xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.examples">
		  <title>Examples</title>

		  <example xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.examples.parapub"><title>Parallel Publication</title>
<programlisting language="orc-demo"><![CDATA[
{- Publish 1 and 2 in parallel -}

1 | 1+1

{-
OUTPUT:PERMUTABLE
1
2
-}
]]></programlisting>
		  </example>

		  <example xml:id="ref.combinators.parallel.examples.parasite"><title>Parallel Site Calls</title>
<programlisting language="orc"><![CDATA[
{- Access two search sites, Google and Yahoo, in parallel.
   
   Publish any results they return.
   
   Since each call may publish a value, the expression
   may publish up to two values.
-}  

Google("cupcake") | Yahoo("cupcake")

{-
NONRUNNABLE
-}
]]></programlisting>
		  </example>
		  
	  </section>
	   
